narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A survey course in American literature. I would not recommend the class to another student unless they were truly interested in reading the particular texts in the course. Otherwise, I would recommend taking a course in American lit more particularly focused on an era of interest for the student

English 127 is a good introduction to America literature. It does a good job of offering a diverse reading list but this comes at the cost of the classics. The reading is manageable and the essays are interesting. Jordan was a great section leader, who made the class interesting and kept us engaged. I would take it again.
